<subSubSection id="09AB84DA421F8947FF755E20FE1CC67F" pageId="24" pageNumber="34" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="410ED751421F8947FF755E20FE98C5C5" blockId="24.[227,348,1391,1417]" box="[227,348,1391,1417]" pageId="24" pageNumber="34">
<heading id="1A46603D421F8947FF755E20FE98C5C5" bold="true" box="[227,348,1391,1417]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="24" pageNumber="34" reason="3">
<emphasis id="73C50B43421F8947FF755E20FE98C5C5" bold="true" box="[227,348,1391,1417]" pageId="24" pageNumber="34">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="410ED751421F8947FF755EECFE1CC67F" blockId="24.[227,1437,1442,1593]" pageId="24" pageNumber="34">
Genus of the family 
<taxonomicName id="86B1ACD2421F8947FE7F5EEDFD41C5F0" authorityName="Becker &amp; House" authorityYear="1993" box="[489,645,1442,1468]" class="Cephalopoda" family="Koenenitidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ammonoidea" pageId="24" pageNumber="34" phylum="Mollusca" rank="family">Koenenitidae</taxonomicName>
with extremely discoidal, subinvolute to involute conch; venter rounded in all stages. Suture line with wide external lobe, moderately high median saddle, narrowly V-shaped E2 lobe, U-shaped or V-shaped lateral lobe and rounded umbilical lobes. Suture line formula (E 
<subScript id="DD35D514421F8947FF685D64FEC3C675" attach="left" box="[254,263,1579,1593]" fontSize="6" pageId="24" pageNumber="34">2</subScript>
E 
<subScript id="DD35D514421F8947FEB65D64FEEDC675" attach="left" box="[288,297,1579,1593]" fontSize="6" pageId="24" pageNumber="34">1</subScript>
E 
<subScript id="DD35D514421F8947FED45D64FE8FC675" attach="left" box="[322,331,1579,1593]" fontSize="6" pageId="24" pageNumber="34">2</subScript>
) L U 
<subScript id="DD35D514421F8947FE1F5D64FE56C675" attach="left" box="[393,402,1579,1593]" fontSize="6" pageId="24" pageNumber="34">2</subScript>
: U 
<subScript id="DD35D514421F8947FE205D64FE7BC675" attach="left" box="[438,447,1579,1593]" fontSize="6" pageId="24" pageNumber="34">1</subScript>
I.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
