<subSubSection id="09AB84DA421F8947FF755C3CFE5BC842" pageId="24" pageNumber="34" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="410ED751421F8947FF755C3CFE91C7C1" blockId="24.[227,341,1907,1933]" box="[227,341,1907,1933]" pageId="24" pageNumber="34">
<heading id="1A46603D421F8947FF755C3CFE91C7C1" bold="true" box="[227,341,1907,1933]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="24" pageNumber="34" reason="3">
<emphasis id="73C50B43421F8947FF755C3CFE91C7C1" bold="true" box="[227,341,1907,1933]" pageId="24" pageNumber="34">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="410ED751421F8947FF755CE9FE5BC842" blockId="24.[227,1437,1957,2062]" pageId="24" pageNumber="34">
<taxonomicName id="86B1ACD2421F8947FF755CE9FEA1C7F3" authorityName="Wedekind" authorityYear="1913" box="[227,357,1958,1983]" class="Cephalopoda" family="Koenenitidae" genus="Koenenites" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ammonoidea" pageId="24" pageNumber="34" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="73C50B43421F8947FF755CE9FEA1C7F3" box="[227,357,1958,1983]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="34">Koenenites</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the only genus of the family 
<taxonomicName id="86B1ACD2421F8947FD6F5CEAFC51C7F3" authorityName="Becker &amp; House" authorityYear="1993" box="[761,917,1957,1983]" class="Cephalopoda" family="Koenenitidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ammonoidea" pageId="24" pageNumber="34" phylum="Mollusca" rank="family">Koenenitidae</taxonomicName>
in which the conch has a rounded venter. 
<taxonomicName id="86B1ACD2421F8947FF755C81FEA1C7AB" authorityName="Wedekind" authorityYear="1913" box="[227,357,1998,2023]" class="Cephalopoda" family="Koenenitidae" genus="Koenenites" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ammonoidea" pageId="24" pageNumber="34" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="73C50B43421F8947FF755C81FEA1C7AB" box="[227,357,1998,2023]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="34">Koenenites</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, along with 
<taxonomicName id="86B1ACD2421F8947FD965C82FD77C7AB" authorityName="Gurich" authorityYear="1896" box="[512,691,1997,2023]" class="Cephalopoda" family="Koenenitidae" genus="Hoeninghausia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ammonoidea" pageId="24" pageNumber="34" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="73C50B43421F8947FD965C82FD77C7AB" box="[512,691,1997,2023]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="34">Hoeninghausia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, also has the simplest suture line in the family with only two umbilical lobes.
</paragraph>
